    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Fair enough :) I see your point of view, even though I belong to the other philosophy school, that doesn't see much of a problem in altering and modifying existing maps to make them better. As it says in its name, \"OpenRA\" is about open content, so why not play with it ^_^\n\nJust for the record, I used to hate this map, until the Heavy version showed up, making it possible to have a decent economy, and a pleasant game. Therefore, I think improving existing maps over and over is IMO a good thing, in order to keep them appealing, and alive :) \n\nBut like I said I totally understand your stance, and yeah maybe it's even better to create new maps that are inspired from the originals, and adding new ideas to them. The Map Design Contest is a good way to do this, kudos to that :) \n"
  },
